cidence) leads to significant miscalculations when the cylinder cross-section\nbecomes non-circular. Moreover, the elliptical cylinder experiences, in\naddition to the acoustic radiation force, a radiation torque that vanishes for\nthe circular cylinder case. The application of the formalism presented here may\nbe extended to other 2D surfaces of arbitrary shape.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Mar 2016 21:11:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-21"}
