{"id":"1603.03503","submitter":"Peter Thomas PhD","authors":"Youngmin Park and Kendrick M. Shaw and Hillel J. Chiel and Peter J.\n  Thomas","title":"The Infinitesimal Phase Response Curves of Oscillators in Piecewise\n  Smooth Dynamical Systems","comments":"37 pages, 10 figures","journal-ref":"PARK, Y., SHAW, K., CHIEL, H., & THOMAS, P. (2018). The\n  infinitesimal phase response curves of oscillators in piecewise smooth\n  dynamical systems. European Journal of Applied Mathematics, 1-36.\n  doi:10.1017/S0956792518000128","doi":"10.1017/S0956792518000128","report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The asymptotic phase $\\theta$ of an initial point $x$ in the stable manifold\nof a limit cycle identifies the phase of the point on the limit cycle to which\nthe flow $\\phi_t(x)$ converges as $t\\to\\infty$. The infinitesimal phase\nresponse curve (iPRC) quantifies the change in timing due to a small\nperturbation of a limit cycle trajectory. For a stable limit cycle in a smooth\ndynamical system the iPRC is the gradient $\\nabla_x(\\theta)$ of the phase\nfunction, which can be obtained via the adjoint of the variational equation.\nFor systems with discontinuous dynamics, the standard approach to obtaining the\niPRC fails. We derive a formula for the infinitesimal phase response curves\n(iPRCs) of limit cycles occurring in piecewise smooth (Filipov) dynamical\nsystems of arbitrary dimension, subject to a transverse flow condition.\nDiscontinuous jumps in the iPRC can occur at the boundaries separating\nsubdomains, and are captured by a linear matching condition. The matching\nmatrix, $M$, can be derived from the saltation matrix arising in the associated\nvariational problem. For the special case of linear dynamics away from\nswitching boundaries, we obtain an explicit expression for the iPRC. We present\nexamples from cell biology (Glass networks) and neuroscience (central pattern\ngenerator models). We apply the iPRCs obtained to study synchronization and\nphase-locking in piecewise smooth limit cycle systems in which synchronization\narises solely due to the crossing of switching manifolds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Mar 2016 02:26:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 29 Jul 2017 04:16:30 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 12 Apr 2018 02:36:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-13"}
